.subtitle MOVE LOGICAL UNITS
.index ISIS LOGICAL UNIT
.spacing 1
.upper case
.left margin 10
.right margin 75
.fill
.justify
.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
MOVING LOGICAL UNITS IN ISIS SLOTS
.BREAK 
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE 
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This procedure allows a user to move a logical unit within an ISIS slot
and from one slot to another.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
1. Access DDT in target node.
2. "SYS" license in DDT required to move L.U.
3. Knowledge of TYM files.
.fill
.justify
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. SCOPE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The ability to move logical units enhances our trouble shooting needs.  The
specialist can move a L.U. to a spare slot and load an inactive and online
slot diagnostic.
.skip 1
.left margin 10
IV.  PROCEDURE
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  Check the TYM file for the Logical Unit (L.U.) that is to be moved.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  Log into DDT in the target node.                                     
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  At the "slot_#" prompt, put in the number of the slot currently assigned
to L.U. that is to be moved.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
4.  Once the "*" prompt is displayed the user is connected to the slot.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
5.  Type: ?LU.  This will display all the logical units assigned to the
slot and hardware referenced to each in the TYM file.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
6.  Type in ?TRAN.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
7.  At the "Source L.U." prompt, type in the number of the logical unit to
be moved.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
8.  At the "Destination slot" prompt, type in the number of the slot to  
which the L.U. is being moved.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
9.  At the "Destination L.U." prompt, type in the number of the slot to which
the L.U. is to be moved.
.skip 1
.left margin 19
.indent -1
(All responses are expected in hexadecimal)
.skip 1
.left margin 19
.indent -1
(The source and destination slot can be the same)
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
10. At the * prompt, issue the _^ (up arrow) and the destination slot number
that L.U. was moved to.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5      
11. Type ?LU to verify that the L.U. was moved and that it has the correct
number.
.skip 2
.left margin 15
WARNING:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
In some interfaces, when transferring the L.U. back to the source slot, the
slot will halt.  It will be necessary to restart it using the "E" command
(EXECUTE).
