.fill
.justify
.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
LOADING FILES TO ELF
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
ELF is used to generate a binary image of code on a disk or tape and load
that image into a engine through a network.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  The purchase of the ELF software and all necessary hardware relative to
its operation.
.left margin 18
2.  Access to ELF document.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  Access to mainframe host computers that stores the production code of
the network.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 14
I.  To Set Up ELF for Gateway Access:
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  Log into ELF with the appropriate login string.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  Enter all commands at the (:) prompts.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  At the first prompt, type "GATEWAY".  This command must be used by those
without a TYMCOM-X system running on their network, before any 'CREATE'
command is used.  This tells ELF that it must login through a gateway
before it can actually login to the TYMCOM-X to retrieve data.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  Next prompt is 'GATEWAY USERNAME HOST'.  Type in the valid username in
the user's network.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  ELF will now prompt "IS THIS AN X.75 GATEWAY?"
.left margin 23
.indent -1   
(Enter 'YES' only if gateway host specified is an X.75 gateway, otherwise
enter 'NO'.)
.skip 2
.left margin 14
II.  To Load a Bound File onto ELF:
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  At the prompt, type: "CR N"  (CREATE NODE)
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  ELF will prompt user with 'DEVICE UNIT ID': Enter the unit ID of the 
device to be written on, ie. "Do".
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  User will be prompt 'FILE ID': This is used to identify the file on a load.
Enter the checksum of the file.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  ELF will display: SHOULD FILE BE WRITTEN IN IMAGE FORMAT?
.left margin 23
.indent -1
(Type 'YES' if you intend to load the file via the bootstrap.)
.left margin 23
.indent -1
(Type 'NO' if file will always be loaded through the ELF.)
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  The user is prompted for the TYMCOM-X login string as follows:
'TYMCOM-X USERNAME,HOST': The user enters the username to be used to log
into the TYMCOM-X in TYMNET where the load data is stored - enter host
number if required.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
6.  User is then prompted 'PASSWORD': Enter password for username just
entered.  Password will not be echoed to the terminal.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
7.  At the 'OBJECT FILE' enter: The name of the file you wish to be
transferred to ELF.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
8.  If user is not prompted for the object file, check to see if gateway
command was issued.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
9.  File will begin to transfer.
.left margin 22
.indent -5
10.  When completed, the (:) prompt will appear again.
.skip 1
.left margin 14
III.  To Load a Slot File onto ELF:
.subtitle
.page
.subtitle LOADII VIA GATEWAY      
.index LOADII VIA GATEWAY      
.spacing 1
.upper case
.right margin 75
.left margin 10
.fill
.justify 
.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
ACCESSING THROUGH GATEWAYS WITH LOADII
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
This procedure deals with the methods by which LOADII can be used to access
slots and nodes through inter-network gateways.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 18
1.  Access to LOADII, Version 2.16 or later.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  Access license to use LOADII through specific gateways.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  Access to LOADII.DOC
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 14
I.  Using LOADII Through a Single Gateway
.skip 1
.left margin 10
.nofill
.nojustify
#...........                                         ...........
#:         :                ............             :         :
#:  HOST   :                :          :             : TARGET  :
#: Running :----------------: GATEWAY  :-------------:  NODE   :
#: LOADII  :                :..........:             :   or    :
#:         :                                         :  Slot   :
#:.........:                                         :.........:
.skip 1
#_^                                    _^                      _^
#_|<--------NETWORK A----------------> _|<------NETWORK B------> _|
#_|                                    _|                      _|
.FILL 
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  Log into a host on which LOADII is available and at the ENTER FUNCTION
prompt, type G.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  Then in response to the ENTER GATEWAY HOST prompt, type the host number
of the desired gateway between the network in which LOADII is resident and
the netwok in which the target node or slot is resident.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  In response then to the ENTER PASSWORD FOR EXTERNAL NET prompt, type the
appropriate password.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  Then continue responding to the LOADII prompts to perform the desired
LOADII function.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  Reference LOADII.DOC for explanations of any error messages which might
be displayed.
.skip 1
.left margin 14
II. Using LOADII Through Multiple Gateways
.skip 1
.left margin 18
Provision has been made in LOADII to build circuits through multiple 
gateways to reach a target which is not accessible through a single
gateway.  Consider the diagram below.
.skip 2
.left margin 14
.nofill
.nojustify
#..........                                       ..........
#:        :         .........       .........     :        :
#: HOST   :         :       :       :       :     : TARGET :
#:Running :---------:GATEWAY:-------:GATEWAY:-----:  NODE  :
#: LOADII :         :.......:       :.......:     :   or   :
#:........:                                       :  SLOT  :
                                                  :........:
.skip 1
#_^                         _^              _^             _^
#_|<---------NETWORK------> _|<---NETWORK-->_|<----NETWORK--->_|
#_|             A           _|       B      _|      C      _|
.FILL
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 18
When a target node or slot in Network C must be accessed by LOADII which is
resident in Network A and more than one gateway must be passed to effect the
access, the LOADII command X can be used to build the necessary circuit.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  Log into a host on which LOADII is available and at the ENTER FUNCTION
prompt, type X.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  In response to the ENTER GATEWAY HOST NUMBER prompt, type the host 
number of the desired gateway between the network in which it is resident
and the first network to be accessed.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  LOADII will then prompt for the function and will continue to prompt for
information relative to the specified function until all necessary 
information has been acquired.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  At this point LOADII will display the following messages:
.skip 1
.left margin 36
.nofill
.nojustify
BUILDING CIRCUIT
CIRCUIT TO GATEWAY BUILT
ENTERING RELAY MODE (CTL)Z TO EXIT
.fill
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  The login banner for the first network entered will now be displayed
followed by that Network's "please log in:" message.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
6.  The LOADII user now may perform normal logins through gateways to 
finally reach the destination network.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
EXAMPLE:
.skip 1
.left margin 21
.nofill
.nojustify
inter-link established from tymnet-4534 to GHR network
please log in: GATEWAY:4;<password>
inter-link established from GHR network to LFS network
please log in:  (CTL)Z
.skip 1
CIRCUIT BUILT
THE LOAD REQUEST HAS BEEN ACKNOWLEDGED
LOADING
##40-XMT      0-RCV      0-LOST
               : 
               :
.fill
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 29
.indent -7
NOTE:  The example shows the circuit being built into the LFS network which,
in the example, is the location of the target node for a load.
.skip 1
.left margin 29
Notice, that once in that network, the (CTL)Z response was entered to cause
LOADII to exit the "RELAY MODE" and exercise the function that was
specified earlier.
