.page
.subtitle
.page
.subtitle LOADING FILE FROM ELF
.index LOADING FILE FROM ELF
.spacing 1
.upper case
.left margin 10
.right margin 75
.fill
.justify
.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
LOADING FILE FROM ECLECTIC LOAD FACILITY
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
To load a node or slot from an ELF facility.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 18
1.  ELF Facility
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  ELF Facility loaded with current code slot and node.
.left margin 18
3.  Access to ELF documentation.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 14
I.  Loading a Node
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  Log into ELF with the appropriate login string.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  At the first prompt, type "LOAD NODE" (L N)
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  ELF will prompt you for input device, ie. 'Do'
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  ELF will now determine if device requested is available.  If not available,
ELF will display ERROR ON DEVICE,UNIT 'UNAVAILABLE'.  If device is available,
ELF will prompt you for 'FILE ADDRESS'.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  Enter file address of the ELF file that is to be loaded.
.left margin 23
.indent -1
(This information is found by doing a 'DIRECTORY' command.)
.left margin 22
.indent -4
6.  After file address has been entered ELF will display the object file
that corresponds with file address requested.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
7.  ELF will ask if this is 'OKAY'.
.LEFT MARGIN 22
If "NO" is entered, ELF will prompt again for the file address.  
.left margin 22
If "YES" is entered, ELF will progress to the next prompt.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
8.  ELF will prompt now for the target node's neighbor node, its kernel host
and line number.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
9.  When the transfer of node code begins ELF will dsiplay the message
"TRANSFER STARTING".  ELF will report number of records transferred.
.left margin 22
.indent -5
10.  When transfer is complete ELF will display: TRANSFER COMPLETE AND NODE
STARTED'.
.LEFT MARGIN 22
.indent -5
11.  The (:) prompt will return when load is completed.
.left margin 22
.indent -5
12.  Type QUIT to exit the ELF.
.skip 1
.left margin 14
II. Loading a Slot
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  Log into ELF with the appropriate login string.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  At the first prompt, type "LOAD SLOT" (L S)
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  Now follow STEPs 3 through 7 in section I.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  Once "YES" is accepted, ELF will prompt for the slot number.  This is 
the slot that is to be loaded.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  ELF will then prompt for kernel host number.  Enter the kernel host
of the node with slot to be loaded.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
6.  ELF will display "TRANSFER STARTING" and "MAC INITIALIZED".
.left margin 22
.indent -4
7.  When the slot is loaded, ELF will display "TRANSFER COMPLETE" and "SLOT
STARTED".
.left margin 22
.indent -4
8.  ELF will return to the (:) prompt when complete.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
9.  Type QUIT to exit ELF.
