.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
CLEARING PORTS IN PROBE
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
To free a job in PROBE to allow access to it.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
1. Must be logged into PROBE.
2. Must have "01" status in PROBE.
.fill
.justify
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  At the PROBE prompt, type: "WHO".  This will list all the users logged into
PROBE with the left hand list indicating the "job label".  This job label will
identify the user to be removed.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  At the next prompt, type: "HANG 'x'" with 'x' being the job label of the
username to be removed.
