.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.BREAK
.skip 2
.center 84
TMCS: FUNCTIONING IN DISPLAY MODE
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This procedure will outline the proper method of setting up TMCS to function
in the DISPLAY mode.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  PROCEDURE 
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  Log into TMCS
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  At the TMCS prompt, type: LIS PRO
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  At the TMCS prompt, type: LIS SEL
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
4.  Check the output from STEP 3 and use the TMCS "RESTORE" and/or
"IGNORE" commands to establish the LIMITS which will be required to 
obtain the DISPLAY coverage that is required.
.skip 1
.left margin 25
.indent -7
NOTE:  It will be impossible to restore anything which is not listed in
       the output from STEP 2.  Consult TMCS documentation for procedure
       for having the PROFILE changed.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
5.  Locate the terminal identifier just to the right of the TMCS user name
in the first line of the output obtained in STEP 2.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
6.  If your terminal is not comparable to the terminal type identified
in STEP 5, use the TMCS "TER" command to set TMCS up for your specific
terminal.
.skip 1
.left margin 24
.indent -6
Type:  TER ? in response to the TMCS prompt to obtain a list of acceptable
terminal types.
.skip 1
.left margin 24
.indent -6
Type:  TER xxxxxxx in response to the TMCS prompt to set TMCS up for
the terminal now in use.  (where xxxxxxx = the terminal type)
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
7.  In response to the TMCS prompt, type: DISPLAY
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
8.  The current NODE, HOST, LINE and LINK statuses will then appear on the 
terminal.
