LOGIN RATE 0
 7 0 0 14 423 0 580
DF 0 REJECTS 0 0 0
83:11:02:25
LOGIN RATE 16
 1 0 0 2 446 0 580
DF 0 REJECTS 0 0 0
83:11:02:40
LOGIN RATE 33
 0 0 0 0 447 0 580
DF 0 REJECTS 0 0 0
.fill
.justify
.skip 1
.left margin 22
The Supervisor takeover is complete when it has all Tymnet I and II nodes
under its control and nothing is in TAKEOVER failure.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
NOTE:  Takeover failure is when a node is stuck in one of its takeover
states.  Tymnet I nodes have five (5) states.  Tymnet II has two takeover
states.  
.skip 1
.left margin 22
On the logger, you'll get the node number of the node in takeover 
failure and which state the node is currently in.  TYMNET I has 
states 0-4.  TYMNET II has state 0 only.  If you cannot correct the
problem with a retake of the upstream neighbor, notify Field
Engineering (FE) of that particular region.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
5.  After the takeover is completed, the following must be accomplished.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
A.  Do a LSTMIN on the Supervisor you have just put to sleep.  Get total
logins.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
B.  Type version on the active Supervisor and get the version of code
running PROBE, KERNEL and SUPER.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
C.  Do an ALL NODES (AN) and LIST SHUTS (LSHUT) and COUNT.  Compare the
LSHUT from the current active Supervisor with the LSHUT from the
Supervisor you have just put to sleep.  There should be no difference
on LSHUT and COUNT.  If there is a different in the COUNT, use the AN
to determine the discrepancy.
