.subtitle GATEWAY FAILURE
.index GATEWAY FAILURE
.spacing 1
.upper case
.left margin 10
.right margin 75
.fill
.justify
.figure 5
.center 84
NETWORK OPERATIONS PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 2
.center 84
GATEWAY FAILURE AND RECOVERY
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
This procedure describes the techniques for trouble-shooting a failure of
a gateway and its recovery.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 21
.indent -3
1. Access to both networks involved with gateway.
.left margin 21
.indent -3
2. Knowledge of TYM files.
.left margin 21
.indent -3    
3. Direct or indirect access to XRAY and DDT in both networks.
.left margin 21
.indent -3
4. DDT license required: L.Halt, L.E., L.SOA
.left margin 21
.indent -3
5. Access to SLSYNC diagnostic.
.left margin 21
.indent -3       
6. Access to loading facility, LOADII and/or ELF.
.left margin 21
.indent -3
7. Access to circuit numbers and Telco trouble numbers.
.left margin 21
.indent -3      
8. Ability to run SLSYNC diagnostic.
.skip 2
.left margin 15
COMMENTS:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
For procedural purposes, we will identify the 2 networks involved by letter.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
^&NET-A will contain the following:\&
a.#GATEWAY HOST NUMBER
b.#GATEWAY SLOT CODE
.fill
.justify
.left margin 37
.indent -19
c.#SYNC LINE TO NET-B (referenced in TYM file for slot with gateway code) 
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
^&NET-B will contain the following:\&
a.#PSEUDO NODE NUMBER
.fill
.justify
.LEFT MARGIN 37
.INDENT -19
b.#SYNC LINE TO NET-A (referenced in TYM file for slot 0 of the REAL NODE that the
gateway is connected to)
.left margin 37
.indent -19
c.#REAL NODE##########(has the physical connection of the sync line for the  
gateway via slot 0.  The PSEUDO NODE will be listed as the neighbor.)
.skip 2
.left margin 15
GENERAL INFO:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
Circuit number on both sides of the gateway is always the same.
Gateway pseudo-node number is always TYMNET I (less than 2000).
.fill
.justify
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE FOR "HOST SHUT"
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  This message indicates that the REAL NODE in NET-B has gone out of the
network or the circuit for the gateway has been lost.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  Verify that the REAL NODE is up by snapping it in PROBE in NET-B.  If
node is down, follow procedure to restore node to a network, once it is back
up, the gateway will come back up.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  If REAL NODE is up, the indication is then that the circuit has been 
lost between NET-A and NET-B.  Turn the circuit over to Telco to test the
line.  If Telco reports no problem found and gateway is still shut, SLSYNC
should be run to determine which end has the problem.  Follow the procedure
"TROUBLE-SHOOTING NON-HARDWIRED INTERNODAL LINES".
.skip 2
.left margin 10
IV.  PROCEDURE FOR "HOST NOT AVAILABLE THROUGH NET"
.skip 1
.left margin 14
COMMENTS:
.SKIP 1
.left margin 18
STEPs IV.2 and IV.3 require access to NET-A utilities which may not be 
available to the user of this procedure.  In such a case, the user should 
contact NET-A's customer service group and request that they perform STEPs
IV.2 and IV.3.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  This message indicates that the node in NET-A containing the gateway    
slot code is out of the network, or that the slot containing the gateway code
has stopped operating.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  To check if node is up, snap it in PROBE in NET-A.  If the node is
down, follow the procedure to bring a node back up.  Once node is back 
up, the gateway will come back up.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
.test page 7
3.  If the node is up, snap the gateway host number in PROBE in NET-A.
If "NO SUCH HOST", the slot is down.  Follow the procedure to bring a
slot back up.  The host will show as "shut" for a moment, once slot is running 
again.  This is the time it takes for it to initialize and establish contact.
Once the host is "ANSWERED" in PROBE, the gateway will be back up.
.subtitle
