INTER-NODAL OCL LINE
.BREAK
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
This procedure describes the techniques for trouble-shooting an inter-nodal
OCL line which is either out of service or providing degraded service.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.LEFT MARGIN 21
.indent -3
.nofill 
.nojustify
1. Access to the LINST.REL test file.
.LEFT MARGIN 21
.INDENT -3
2. Access to a code loading utility, LOADII or ELF.
.LEFT MARGIN 21
.INDENT -3
3. Ability to have breakout box loopbacks set up.
.LEFT MARGIN 21
.INDENT -3
4. Knowledge of which physical node ports connect to the line.
.LEFT MARGIN 21
.INDENT -3
5. Access to PROBE, XRAY and/or TMCS.
.fill
.justify
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
(Diagram A will be referenced in the following steps.)
.skip 1
.left margin 10
.nofill
.nojustify
#............                                      ............ 
#:          :                                      :          :
#:  NODE A  :____________________________________________________________________________:  NODE B  :
#:          :_\                                    /:          :
#:..........: _\____Port x##################Port y____/ :..........:
.fill
.justify 
.left margin 10
.right margin 75
.skip 1
.center 84
Diagram A
.break
.skip 2
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  Using PROBE place a SHUT in the line and using the ND command in XRAY determine if the
number of users on the line is sufficiently low to proceed to STEP 2   
where the line will be taken down.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  Jumper Pin 4 to Pin 11 on a breakout box.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  Remove the cable from Port x of Node A.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
4.  Install the breakout box on Port x but do not connect the cable to the
breakout box.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
5.  Using LOADII or ELF, attempt to load LINTST.REL through Port x of NODE
A.  (The breakout box will act as the target for the load)
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
6.  If the terminal logged into the load utility (LOADII or ELF) displays
any indications of "Lost Data", you are receiving an indication of errors
and NODE A will require servicing.  After servicing has been completed, go
to STEP 14.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
7.  If LINTST.REL loads without losing data, disconnect the breakout box
from Port x and connect the breakout box to the cable end which was initially
disconnected from Port x.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
8.  Terminate any "loading" of LINTST.REL currently underway through NODE A
and attempt to do a load of LINTST.REL through Port y of NODE B.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
9.  If the load utility being used does not indicate any lost data, go to
STEP 11.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
10. If data is being "lost", remove the breakout box from the cable,
disconnect the cable from Port y of NODE B and connect the breakout box
to Port y of NODE B. (Do not connect the cable to the breakout box.)
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
11. Stop and restart the load of LINTST.REL through Port y of NODE B.
If data is still lost, NODE B will require servicing.  If data is not
lost, either the cable is bad or the drivers and/or receivers on Port y
are not able to drive the cable's electrical load.  In either event servicing will be
required.  After the servicing is completed, go to STEP 14.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
12. Make certain that the cable is reconnected to Port x of NODE A and
disconnected from Port y of NODE B.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
13. Connect the breakout box to the cable end removed from Port y but do
not connect the breakout box to Port y.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
14. Terminate any loads which are in progress and restart the loading of
LINTST.REL through Port x of NODE A.  If data is lost during the load,
you may be observing a cable program but you are probably observing an
inability of NODE A to properly drive the cable's electrical load.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
15. After servicing is complete, rerun any tests which failed to verify
the effectiveness of the service effort.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
16. Reconnect the inter-nodal line to the appropriate ports.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
17. Terminate any loads which are underway.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -5
18. Observe the line with PROBE, XRAY or TMCS for any further indications
of problems.
.skip 2
.left margin 15
COMMENTS:
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The procedure used here to trouble-shoot a Memory-Shuffler line will not
cause any interruption of service on the remainder of either node.
