PASSWORD SECURITY
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.  PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
To establish the necessary attitude needed to insure the integrity of our
network access.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  DEFINITIONS
.skip 1
.left margin 18
Password - A collection of characters numbering at least seven (7) and not
more than twenty (20).  At least one non-alpha character will be embedded
in the collection.  A semi-colon or a control-M may not be used.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III.  PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
1.  All passwords will be routinely changed on the first Monday of each month.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
2.  In the event that personnel, who had access to passwords, leave the 
organization, passwords to which they had access will be changed within 
the ensuing eight hours.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
3.  When personnel leave an organization the unit manager will cancel
any individual user names, or operator license the person had sole access
to.  If the unit manager is unavailable, then the next available manager will
be notified of the required changes.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
4.  Passwords will not be transmitted via printed media.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
5.  Passwords will not be disseminated beyond organizational limits except
by the approval of the controlling organization's manager.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
6.  Records of license and password access granted to every individual will
be maintained.
