SHIFT TURNOVER PROCEDURES
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The procedure outlines some of the processes by which an orderly transfer of
responsibility between shifts can be effected.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.nofill
.nojustify
1. A Shift Turnover Form.
2. Access to TMCS
3. A Trouble Log or Trouble Ticket System.
.fill
.justify
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. OVERVIEW
.skip 1
.left margin 18
The purpose of a Shift Turnover procedure is to make it possible for one
network operations shift to replace another shift with the least possible
impact on the operation of the network.  The principal aspects of the
turnover are:
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
1.  Shift Turnover Forms filled out by operations specialists.
.left margin 26
.indent -4
2.  A Problem Log or Ticket System.
.left margin 26
.indent -4
3.  A review of TMCS and/or PROBE indications of the network's health.
.left margin 26
.indent -4
4.  A verbal briefing given by the shift being relieved.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
IV.  PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  During the course of shift, it will become obvious that certain
activities will not be completed during the shift.  Personnel should
make notations on a Shift Turnover Form relative to such activities and
should provide sufficient information for the next shift to take any
necessary action.
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
a.  During the process of the actual shift turnover, the Shift Turnover forms
should be collected from the existing shift personnel and turned over to the
new shift's personnel for review and subsequent action.
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
b.  If the shift going off duty received Shift Turnover Forms from the
shift it replaced and some items on those forms have not been resolved,
those forms should also be turned over to the new shift.
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
c.  Once completed, all Shift Turnover Forms should be kept on file for one
week.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  A review of Trouble Log entries or open Trouble Tickets should be
conducted between the old and new shifts to:
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
a.  Bring outtages to the attention of the new shift.
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
b.  Make the new shift aware of any difficulties in getting existing 
problems cleared.
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
c.  Prevent duplication of effort.
.skip 1
.left margin 26
.indent -4
d.  Preclude the possibility of a problem being allowed to go unresolved.
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  The new shift should cross check the NODE, HOST and LINE OUTTAGES 
reported by TMCS against the current Trouble Log or against the open 
Trouble Tickets to ascertain that all existing anomalies are being
addressed.
