USING TYMCOM OPERATIONS MANAGER
.break
.skip 3
.left margin 10
I.   PURPOSE
.skip 1
.left margin 18
To use TOM to check on a port's status, to put a port in or out of service.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
II.  REQUIREMENTS
.skip 1
.left margin 22
.indent -4
1.  Access to TOM via hardwired port or through the network.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  Status for LEVEL 1 commands.
.skip 2
.left margin 10
III. PROCEDURE
.skip 1
.left margin 14
I.  To check a port's status.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
1.  Log into TOM.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  All prompts are the symbol '>'.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  Type in "ST P _#" to check status of an individual port.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  Type in "ST P _#-_#" to check a range of ports.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
5.  Type in "ST P" to check status of all the ports.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
6.  TOM will list the port numbers and the status for each port requested.
The status is indicated by the following letters: U,D,S,A,V.
.left margin 22
U = UP, D = DOWN, S = SHUT, A = ACTIVE, V = VESTIGIAL
.LEFT MARGIN 22
Active indicates that the port is up and circuit to it exists.  Vestigial
indicates that the port has been shut but still has an active circuit.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
.indent -4
II. To UP or DOWN a port, ie. put them in or out of service.
.skip 1
.left margin 18
1.  Log into TOM.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
2.  All prompts are the symbol '>'.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
3.  Type "GRAB _#_#_#_#_#_#", with _#_#_#_#_#_# being the change license 
password.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
4.  The user will now have the status to up or down a port.
.left margin 22
.indent -4 
5.  Type "UP P _#" or "DOWN P _#" to change the status of one port.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
6.  Type "UP P _#-_#" or "DOWN P _#-_#" to change the status of a range of
ports.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
7.  The DOWN command will cause current users to be dropped when it is 
issued.
.left margin 22
.indent -4
8.  The "SHUT" command may be used in the same way.  This will not affect
current users but will prevent the port from being available for future
assignments.
